(56, 6, 'fikirbuzz', '2022-05-12 12:42:11', 0, 1, 0, 46, 0, 'nca-1010', '', '', 'NCA-1010', 'Compact Fanless x86 Network Appliance with Intel Bay Trail Platform (Atom E3800 CPU)', 'pdf/sample.pdf', 'pdf/sample.pdf', '<ul>\n	<li>Compact form factor</li>\n	<li>Intel Atom E3815 or E3825 CPU (codename Bay Trail)</li>\n	<li>1 x DDR3L SODIMM memory up to 8GB</li>\n	<li>Fanless design</li>\n	<li>Built-in security engine: hardware assisted AES-NI</li>\n	<li>3 x RJ45 GbE LAN ports, 1 x USB 3.0, 1 x USB 2.0, 1 x HDMI port</li>\n	<li>1 x full-length mini-PCIe slot for Wi-Fi/BT/3G connectivity</li>\n	<li>1 x half-length mini-PCIe slot for mSATA</li>\n	<li>1 x antenna hole</li>\n</ul>\n', 'NCA-1010 is Lanner’s revolutionary ultra compact x86 networking system built with Intel® Bay Trail CPU (Atom™ E3815/E3825). The central processor comes with hardware-assisted security mechanisms including AES-NI, allowing only authorized software or data to run on NCA-1010. With built-in instruction commands, NCA-1010 helps manage and secure devices connected to local WiFi network, like a compact entry-level firewall or multi-service gateway.\nDespite its compact size, NCA-1010 delivers rich I/O connectivity and scalability. In terms of scalability, NCA-1010 comes with one HDMI port for high definition display, one console port for device network management, three LAN ports for network connections, two USB ports (one in USB 2.0 and another in USB 3.0 specifications) for external devices, and one antenna hole for signal reception. The rich I/O connectivity makes NCA-1010 a widely deployable system in small area network environments.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 15, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(57, 7, 'fikirbuzz', '2022-05-12 12:44:23', 0, 1, 1, 47, 0, 'fw-7526', '', '', 'FW-7526', 'Fanless Desktop x86 Network Appliance with 4 RJ45 GbE and 2 SFP GbE Ports\n', '', '', '<ul>\n	<li>Intel Atom processor dual-core C2358 or quad-core C2518 (Codenamed Rangeley)</li>\n	<li>Fanless design</li>\n	<li>4 x GbE RJ45 and 2 x GbE SFP ports</li>\n	<li>Supports Intel QuickAssist crypto acceleration</li>\n	<li>Includes Intel&reg; AES-NI new instructions</li>\n	<li>Supports up to 16 GB DDR3 memory</li>\n	<li>Intel i210-IS or i354 LAN controller</li>\n	<li>Support 1 pair Gen.2 LAN Bypass</li>\n	<li>1 x mini-PCIe with SIM slot for wireless expansion</li>\n	<li>Optional rack mounting kit support</li>\n</ul>\n', 'Lanner FW-7526 is driven by Intel Atom C2358 or C2518 CPU (dual-core or quad-core), ideal for entry-level UTM, firewall, VPN and virtual CPE in small-medium enterprise settings due to its low power consumption and steady performance. The platform is accompanied by Intel QuickAssist Crypto Acceleration technology for cryptographic boost. In addition, the processor is built in with Intel AES-NI (Advanced Encryption Standard – New Instruction) to further enhance the network data encryption for higher security level.\nFunctioning as a virtual CPE, FW-7526 comes with four RJ-45 GbE ports and two SFP GbE ports for network connections. The device also features one pair of Lanner’s Gen2 LAN bypass for network traffic reliability.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 15, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
