(194, 41, 'fikirbuzz', '2022-05-13 13:46:55', 0, 1, 0, 20, 0, 'nca-1611', '', '', 'NCA-1611', 'NEBS-compliant Desktop vCPE Appliance for SD-WAN and SD-Security\n', '', '', '<ul>\n	<li>Intel&reg; Xeon&reg; D-1500 Series 4~8 Cores CPU (Broadwell-DE NS)</li>\n	<li>6x GbE RJ45, 2x SFP (By SKU), 2x SFP+ (By SKU), 1 Pair of Gen3 Bypass (By SKU)</li>\n	<li>4x 288-pin Long DIMM, DDR4 2133MHz, 64GB (ECC) / 128GB (RDIMM)</li>\n	<li>Intel&reg; QuickAssist Technology at 40Gbps</li>\n	<li>1x RJ45 Console, 2x USB 3.0, Optional 1x 2.5&rdquo; HDD/SSD Drive Bay and 1 x SATADOM</li>\n	<li>Virtualization-ready Design with SR-IOV Support</li>\n	<li>2x Mini-PCIe Half Size, One w/ SIM Holder (PCIe/USB2.0)</li>\n	<li>90W 1+1 Redundant PSUs</li>\n</ul>\n', 'The 8-core NCA-1611 is a NEBS-compliant desktop network appliance built with Intel Xeon D-1500 Series CPU (codenamed Broadwell-DE NS). It is virtualization-ready, features 8x LAN ports, 2x 10G SFP+, up to 128GB system memory, and is optimized with SR-IOV, allowing a device, such as a network adapter, to separate access to its resources among various PCIe Virtual Functions.\n\nIn addition to being NEBS-compliant, the NCA-1611 is also K.21 certified. Its carrier-grade design comes with Intel® QuickAssist Technology at 40G, ideal for SD-VPN and SD-Security deployment scenarios. For wireless connectivity, the NCA-1611 offers dual mini-PCIe (one with SIM reader), supporting Wi-Fi, LTE, IPMI, simplifying service deployment at remote sites and most SME office branches.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 21, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
