(1222, 50, 'fikirbuzz', '2022-06-20 12:07:06', 0, 1, 1, 11, 0, 'lec-6041', '', '', 'LEC-6041', 'IEC 61850-3 Wide Temperature ICS Cyber Security Gateway with Intel Atom CPU\n', 'pdf/LEC-6041-datasheet.pdf', 'pdf/LEC-6041_User_Manuel.pdf', '<ul>\n	<li>Wide Temperature ICS Cyber Security Box PC</li>\n	<li>IEC 61850-3 and IEEE 1613 Certified</li>\n	<li>Intel&reg; Atom&trade; x7-E3950 or x5-E3930 CPU</li>\n	<li>5 x GbE LAN with 1 pair bypass, 2 x GbE SFP</li>\n	<li>Onboard TPM support</li>\n	<li>HDMI display output</li>\n	<li>Mini-PCIe with SIM card slot for 4G-LTE support</li>\n	<li>2 x USB 3.0 and 2 x Isolated RS232</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div id=\"accel-snackbar\" style=\"left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, 0px); top: 50px;\">&nbsp;</div>\n', 'Lanner LEC-6041, being the successor of LEC-6021, is designed to protect the communication in both IT and OT domains. LEC-6041 Series is empowered by Intel Atom x7-E3950 or x5-E3930 for low power consumption and high processing performance. As a rugged firewall deployed in challenging environments, LEC-6041 comes with IEC 61850-3 and IEEE 1613 certification, as well as 1.5 KV magnetic isolation protections for LAN port and 15KV ESD Protection for I/O ports. The system can operate in a wide range of operating temperature from -40°C to 70°C. All of the hardware designs assure that the security gateway LEC-6041 will never have downtime while operating in hazardous surroundings such as OT environment.\n\n', 'Intel Atom x7-E3950 or x5-E3930', 'SoC', 'AMI SPI Flash BIOS', 'DDR3L, 1866 MHz', '8 GB', '1 x 204-pin SODIMM', '1 x SATA connector with 2.5” drive bay (optional)', '', '1 pair Bypass', '', '', '2 x Type A', '', 'Phoenix contact 6-pin connector with lock', '', '1x mini-PCIe with 1 SIM card for 4G LTE module (USB & PCIe signal)', 'Internal reset button', '', '', '-40°C to 85°C', '-40°C to 70°C', '5% to 95% (non-condensing)', '160 mm x 166 mm x 53.5 mm (6.30', '1.6 kg (3.52 lbs)', 'Watchdog timer 256 level time interval system reset, so